	<h3>	
			<a  href="/sport/olympics/9444515/London-2012-Olympics-Games-comedy-provokes-few-titters-as-our-leading-cynics-replace-sneers-with-cheers.html">Comics' Olympic sneers turn to cheers</a>
		</h3>

	<div class="picleft containerdiv ">
		<a  href="/sport/olympics/9444515/London-2012-Olympics-Games-comedy-provokes-few-titters-as-our-leading-cynics-replace-sneers-with-cheers.html"><img src="http://i.telegraph.co.uk/multimedia/archive/02295/mccartney_2295990g.jpg" alt="Olympic comedy provokes few titters as even our leading cynics replace sneers with cheers for London 2012" border="0" width="140" height="87" />
							<span class="cornerimageblogleft">&nbsp;</span></a>
		</div>
<p>
<strong>Jim White</strong>: Everything was in standard comedy working order. Except, it 
  seemed, the London 2012 Olympics. 
</p>
